#: ../../Flocculation/Floc_Design.rst:116
msgid "**What are Baffles?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Flocculation/Floc_Design.rst:118
msgid ""
"Now that we know how to measure collision potential with head loss, we "
"need a way to actually generate head loss. While both major or minor "
"losses can be the design basis, it generally makes more sense to use "
"major losses only for very low-flow flocculation (lab-scale) and minor "
"losses for higher flows, as flocculation with minor losses tends to be "
"more space-efficient. Since this book focuses on town and village-scale "
"water treatment (5 L/S to 120 L/S), we will use minor losses as our "
"design basis."
msgstr ""

